results.name: Decimal expansion of the twin prime constant associated with the binary constant in A164292.
comment: If twin prime conjecture is false then this twin prime constant is rational! As a counterpart if it is not rational, the conjecture is true.
If the conjecture is proved by other means, it will remain to see if it is irrational or transcendental.
results.author: _Carlos Alves_, Aug 12 2009
